-- Thai TUF may need to raise equity after debt-fuelled Bumble Bee buy-CEO
-- By Manunphattr Dhanananphorn
-- Fri Dec 19, 2014 12:22AM EST
-- None



BANGKOK, Dec 19 (Reuters) - Thai Union Frozen Products PCL (TUF) <TUF.BK> may need to raise equity capital to lower its debt-to-equity ratio after a $1.5 billion acquisition of U.S. tuna producer Bumble Bee Seafoods, the company's chief executive said on Friday.

TUF's debt-to-equity ratio will more than double to 2.0 from 0.8 after the acquisition, Thai Union's President and Chief Executive Thiraphong Chansiri told reporters. [ID:nL3N0U30J0]  The company would target a return to a debt-to-equity ratio of 1 in the future, he said.